        "user": "How does \"transformer (architecture)\" differ from MoE (Mixture of Experts)?",
        "assistant": "A **Transformer architecture** and **MoE (Mixture of Experts)** differ because they refer to different design ideas:\n\n> A **Transformer** is a sequence-processing neural network architecture built around self-attention and feed-forward layers.  \n> **MoE** is a technique for scaling neural networks by routing inputs to a subset of specialized “expert” sub-networks.\n\nThey are not mutually exclusive: many modern models are **MoE Transformers**.\n\n| Aspect | Transformer | MoE |\n|---|---|---|\n| What it is | A neural network architecture | A scaling/module design technique |\n| Core idea | Use multi-head self-attention to relate positions in a sequence | Use a router/gating network to choose among multiple expert networks |\n| Main mechanism | Self-attention + feed-forward layers | Sparse expert selection |\n| Sequence modeling | Designed to process sequences in parallel | Not specifically a sequence model by itself |\n| Typical use | Language models, translation, vision, multimodal models | Scaling model capacity efficiently |\n| Can combine? | Yes | Yes — MoE is often inserted into Transformer layers |\n\nIn a standard **dense Transformer**, every token usually passes through the same feed-forward sublayer.\n\nIn an **MoE Transformer**, the feed-forward sublayer may be replaced by multiple expert networks. For each token, a router chooses only a few experts, such as the top 1 or top 2.\n\nSo instead of:\n\n> token → one shared feed-forward network\n\nan MoE layer does something like:\n\n> token → router → selected expert(s) → output\n\nThe key difference is:\n\n> A Transformer defines how tokens interact using attention, while MoE defines how computation is distributed across multiple expert subnetworks.\n\nSo MoE is best understood as an architectural component or scaling strategy that can be used **inside** a Transformer, rather than a direct replacement for the Transformer architecture itself.",
